loudly and repeatedly.
</P>
<P>
   In March 1998, for example, Madeleine Albright, the secretary of
state, promised that ``we are not going to stand by and watch the
Serbian authorities do in Kosovo what they can no longer get away
with doing in Bosnia.''
</P>
<P>
   Mrs. Albright also said, that same month, ``The time to stop the
killing is now, before it spreads.'' Yet Clinton, like America's
allies in Europe, dithered.
</P>
<P>
   Second, consider that cozy phrase in the president's Saturday
