</P>
<P>
   Just at the moment, Clinton is preparing to deploy an
anti-missile defense system. But he has not publicly explained why
he has dropped his old opposition to this scheme, or what he means
to do about the Anti-Ballistic Missile treaty, which is relevant to
the nuclear balance with Russia and which may now have to be
renegotiated.
</P>
<P>
   Clinton is a brilliant student who thinks he can succeed by
pulling an all-nighter at the last minute. This is not the best way
to conduct American foreign policy.
</P>
<P>
   But, even though the Kosovo example is typical, it stands out
