sign of the inarticulate and an innovative abbreviation is prized
above all else. The protocol of informality that marks electronic
communication for Andrew Walker, 12, aka Off Cspring, and millions
of others has set off a debate about whether the Internet serves to
invigorate language or strip it of its expressive power. By Amy
Harmon. (1200 words)
