<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   STAR-WARS (Washington) _ In 1983 President Ronald Reagan
envisioned an elaborate space-based shield known as ``Star Wars''
to protect U.S. cities against a doomsday nuclear missile attack.
While such a defense has remained elusive for the last 16 years,
the Clinton administration is edging closer to fulfilling Reagan's
dream. By ERIC ROSENBERG. (Filed Thursday.)
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN (Washington) _ President Clinton has stressed
that he wants to leave a legacy other than his impeachment. To
achieve that, his actions now must benefit the people, safeguard
the republic and demonstrate that he can be trusted. We look at how
the country has survived other weak presidencies. By ROBERT E.
THOMPSON. (Filed Wednesday.)
</P>
