<HEADLINE>
MOISTURIZER FITS LIKE A GLOVE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients)  
( Also moving on ``l'' lifestyle wire). 
 
 
By BARBARA DE WITT  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   &LR; LOS ANGELES _ Plastic gloves are better than nothing when
you're scrubbing walls with harsh detergent or polishing silver,
but the liquid cleaners always seems to drip inside the gloves. To
avoid the itchy chemical reactions or to protect your nails from
paint or oil stains, slip your hands into the lotion called Gloves
in a Bottle. It isn't sticky like some other products, and lasts
for about four hours. And best of all, Miz Hot Tips discovered the
product acts like a paraffin wax treatment at a salon to
temporarily lock in moisture and make your hands feel softer.
</P>
<P>
   Gloves in a Bottle costs $4.95 for 2 ounces (about 60
applications), at Home Depot; Bed, Bath, and Beyond; and Sally
Beauty Supply stores.
</P>
<P>
   FRESH FROM THE FREEZER: For years (and years) we've been putting
baking soda in our garbage pails, down our garbage disposals and
keeping an open box in the fridge to absorb odors, even though it
was originally designed for baking. After 139 years, Arm &AMP; Hammer
finally recognized what we !ital!really!off! use it for and has
produced a new box with the same product called Arm &AMP; Hammer Baking
Soda Fridge &AMP; Freezer. The bright blue box is designed with cloth
filters that expose more baking soda (sodium bicarbonate), plus
it's got a patented flow-through action to absorb and lock in tough
odors, which means food will taste even fresher than before. No
matter which box you buy _ the standard baking soda or the Fridge &AMP;
Freezer variety _ you're supposed to replace it every six months.
</P>
<P>
   IF ONLY FLUFFY COULD FLUSH:!off! Potty training for kids is
difficult, but cats refuse to sit on the toilet, much less put the
lid down when they're finished. However, cleaning their sandbox is
a bit easier with a new cat litter called Scoop 'N Flush by Cat's
Pride. It's made from recycled paper _ just like toilet paper _
dissolves quickly in the toilet bowl, won't clog pipes, yet feels
like traditional clay cat litters.
</P>
<P>
   Miz Hot Tips also liked its wild cherry fragrance and the news
that it's endorsed by the American Humane Association. Scoop 'N
Flush costs $5.99 for a 7-pound box at supermarkets and pet
stores. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
