owner of Maine-based Bath Iron Works. In 1998, the company earned
$364 million, a 14.4 percent boost over 1997. GD has become a
darling of Wall Street, but some people in Maine aren't buying it.
They are angry that the state legislature and the city of Bath have
promised the cash-rich company tax breaks worth $198 million.
(Filed at 12:40.) Davant
