</HEADLINE>
 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients)  The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following stories
today for use by NYTimes News Service clients. They will move in
the ``e'' entertainment news file. For questions, contact Bob
McCarthy at the Daily News, (818) 713-3665. 
 
 
HOT TIPS (Los Angeles) _ A moisturizing lotion called Gloves in a
Bottle is a second line of defense for scrubbing hands. By Barbara
De Witt. 
 
 
DIGITAL-LA (Los Angeles) _ MGM Home Entertainment is releasing a
DVD-ROM version of the action feature ``Ronin'' for home computers.
``There's almost nothing out there for DVD-ROM,'' says MGM Home
Entertainment marketing manager Dave Miller. ``You've got guys out
there with 300-MHz, 400-MHz machines and nothing to watch on
them.'' By David Bloom. 
 
 
NEW-GAMES (Los Angeles) _ A look at the new games for play systems.
By David Bloom. 
 
 
TV-SERIES (Los Angeles _ Think there aren't any TV series left to
be turned into movie franchises? Think again. By Glenn Whipp. 
 
 
BEAVIS-CREATOR (Los Angeles) _ Mike Judge of ``Beavis and
Butt-head'' fame incorporates small observations about people in
his live-action feature debut ``Office Space.'' By Marla Matzer. 
 
 
AFI-HOFFMAN (Los Angeles) _ Dustin Hoffman, one of the most
influential actors of his generation, is presented with the
American Film Institute's 27th Life Achievement Award. By Bob
Strauss. 

