   Separate budgets move daily with spot news, features, sports and
commentary.
</P>
<P>
   If you have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the
Cox News Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   COKE-WATER _ ATLANTA _ The Coca-Cola Co., the nation's leader in
carbonated soft drinks, will begin selling bottled water in the
United States this year. The water, to be sold in a light blue
plastic bottle, is called Dasani. It's expected to be available
nationwide before this summer. Coke already sells bottled water
overseas, but the 113-year-old company has long been reluctant to
add water to its line of soft drinks in the United States. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   COKE-WATER-HEALTH _ Is bottled water better for you? It can have
fewer impurities than tap water, but often those are minuscule
differences and many drink bottled water for taste. Health
officials are concerned that drinking too much bottled water will
mean kids and adults aren't getting enough flouride. And health
regulations are no more stringent for bottled water than tap.
(Guthrie, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 12-15.
</P>
<P>
   HOMEDEPOT-INTERNET _ Home Depot Inc. (HD) is likely to begin
selling home-improvement products over the Internet in this year's
second half but doesn't expect any immediate surge of business,
Arthur M. Blank, chief executive officer, said. Asked about the
potential for online sales, he said: ``I don't see that being a
significant sales mover for us for a very long period of time.'' He
said Home Depot customers typically want to browse the stores and
get advice from clerks before buying. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   KIWI _ ATLANTA _ Kiwi Air has a couple of planes repossessed,
leaving it with only 4 in the air and its recovery plans going
nowhere fast. Checking for any changes in its Atlanta-Newark
service. (Thurston, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   REALTORS _ President of the National Board of Realtors talks
about the use of technology and what it would take to address a
problem that irks agents and Realtors everywhere _ a national MLS
system that would include street addresses and other specifics.
(Harte, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   ONLINE-NEWSPAPERS _ Peter Winter keynotes online newspaper
forum. Message: when it comes to the Web, newspaper content isn't
as important as the building a unique Internet brand which contains
that content. (such as AccessAtlanta). (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
