   OLYMPICS
</P>
<P>
   OLY-ATLANTA-GIFTS _ ATLANTA _ USOC executive director Dick
Schultz said Friday that, with more frequent media reports of
gift-giving by ACOG, Atlanta officials must come clean with
specific information on its dealings with the IOC. To date, ACOG
says it has nothing to report. But the USOC, which will submit
ACOG's information to the IOC, wants to hear about the gifts and
extra plane tickets obtained by IOC members. (Turner, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   OLY-DALLAS _ Dick Young, who won a gold medal in the 4x400 meter
relay, is now a Dallas businessman and on the board to bring the
2012 Olympic Games to that city. As did three other former
Olympians, Young expressed dismay about the current scandals
rocking the International Olympic Committee and several host
cities, but not surprise. (Maher, Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
<P>
   BASEBALL
</P>
<P>
   BBN-BRAVES-GALLARAGA _ LAKJE BUENA VISTA, Fla. _ More reaction
from Braves players to news that Andres Galarraga will miss the
season as he undergoes cancer treatment. (Rogers, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   BBO-GALLARAGA-DOCS _ ATLANTA _ Doctors said Friday Galarraga has
stage 2 lymphoma (out of 4 stages), which means the lymph nodes
could be affected, but are no less optimistic about his recovery.
(Kim, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
