achieved their success this season by blending a group of no-name
players. For a school that has been rocked by several recent
football controversies, the Auburn basketball team is offering a
pleasant diversion. (Bradley, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   BKC-UGA-JIRSA _ ATHENS, Ga. _ Despite clear problems with the
Georgia basketball team, athletics director Vince Dooley said
flatly Friday that he will not fire coach Ron Jirsa. The team
appeared to have one of its worst performances of the season in
Wednesday's loss at Kentucky. The Bulldogs were overmatched against
the Wildcats,but also appeared to have suffered from a lack of
effort. With an NCAA berth out of the question, can Jirsa, who has
received heat for the team's performance throughout the season,
rally the team in time to salvage the remainder of the regular
season? (Towers, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   GYMNASTICS
</P>
<P>
   GYM-UGA-MICHIGAN _ Coverage of the top-ranked Georgia gymnastics
team vs. Michigan, 7:30 p.m. (Brice, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   TRACK AND FIELD
</P>
<P>
   RUN-FAIRFAX _ FAIRFAX, Va. _ Coverage of Friday's indoor track
meet, the third of a four-meet series culminating next week with
the championships at the Georgia Dome in Atlanta. (Fish, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
