<HEADLINE>
UCLA HIRES FOOTBALL ASSISTANT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JON WILNER  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ UCLA has hired John Pearce as an assistant coach
in charge of defensive ends. He replaces defensive coordinator Nick
Aliotti, who Friday accepted a similar post with Oregon after one
tumultuous year at UCLA.
</P>
<P>
   Aliotti's young defense struggled throughout the season,
yielding 28 points per game, and he was publicly criticized by
Bruins coach Bob Toledo after the Oregon State game.
</P>
<P>
   ``(The criticism) obviously had an effect,'' said Aliotti, who
is close friends with Ducks coach Mike Bellotti. ``I'd be lying if
I said it didn't. You need to go to work every day and feel good
about yourself and the people you're around. That situation was not
there. I just didn't feel I had the support.''
</P>
<P>
   Toledo has not named a defensive coordinator. A source said
linebackers coach Marc Dove and secondary coach Bob Field are the
leading candidates.
</P>
<P>
   Pearce was an assistant coach at Texas A&AMP;M during Toledo's
tenure (1989-93) as offensive coordinator.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
