   &QL; 
AMWEST (Tempe, Ariz.) _ An buyout offer by United Airlines is most
likely on the table, but even if the America West board wanted to
take cash, the deal would face an obstacle-filled course of
problems, chief among them union interests. By MAX JARMAN. Story
will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
RAID - Acting on a tip from an informant, immigration officials
raided a motel north of downtown Chandler on Friday and apprehended
77 suspected illegal aliens who had spent the night in four tiny
rooms. In July 1997, the Border Patrol and Chandler police
apprehended 432 illegal immigrants during a five-day period. That
operation resulted in charges of civil-rights violations from
U.S.-born Hispanics and legal immigrants and a $35 million federal
lawsuit which recently has been settled. By JANIE MAGRUDER. Story
will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
