<P>
   BIZ-HOMEOWNERS (Orangetown, N.Y.) _ Houses are the slow-moving
steamships of assets. Prices of existing homes went up 5 percent in
1996 and 4.8 percent in 1997, says the National Association of
Realtors. Adjusting for inflation, the resale values of existing
single-family homes have hardly budged since 1980. By Richard
Korman. (Moved).
